{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "# Semantic Email Search — Mini Spec\n\n**Parent spec:** Email Viewer v1.0  \n**Feature:** Semantic search via OpenAI embeddings + pgvector  \n**Scope:** Additive — no breaking changes to existing schema or routes\n\n---\n\n## What We're Building\n\nA search experience where users can describe what they're looking for in natural language and get back relevant emails — even when the exact words don't match. Layered on top of (not replacing) the existing keyword search.\n\n---\n\n## Schema Changes\n\n### 1. Enable pgvector\n\n```sql\nCREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector;\n```\n\n### 2. Add embedding column to emails table\n\n```sql\nALTER TABLE emails\n  ADD COLUMN embedding vector(1536),\n  ADD COLUMN embedding_generated_at TIMESTAMPTZ;\n```\n\n`vector(1536)` matches OpenAI's `text-embedding-3-small` output dimensions.  \n`embedding_generated_at` tracks processing state — null means not yet embedded.\n\n### 3. Add HNSW index for fast similarity search\n\n```sql\nCREATE INDEX idx_emails_embedding\n  ON emails\n  USING hnsw (embedding vector_cosine_ops)\n  WITH (m = 16, ef_construction = 64);\n```\n\nHNSW is preferred over IVFFlat for this use case — no training step required and handles incremental inserts cleanly.\n\n---\n\n## What Gets Embedded\n\nConcatenate these fields into a single string before sending to OpenAI:\n\n```\nSubject: {subject}\nFrom: {sender}\n{body_plain_text truncated to 6000 characters}\n```\n\n- Use `body_plain_text` over `body_html` — cleaner signal, no tag noise\n- Truncate to stay within the 8192 token limit of `text-embedding-3-small`\n- Strip excessive whitespace and newlines before embedding\n\n---\n\n## Embedding Pipeline\n\nEmbeddings are generated **asynchronously** — never on the ingest request path.\n\n```\nEmail saved to DB\n      │\n      ▼\nQueue job (BullMQ / pg-boss / etc.)\n      │\n      ▼\nWorker pulls emails WHERE embedding IS NULL\n      │\n      ▼\nCalls OpenAI Embeddings API (batch up to 100 at a time)\n      │\n      ▼\nUPDATE emails SET embedding = $1, embedding_generated_at = now()\nWHERE id = $2\n```\n\n### Worker implementation notes\n\n- **Batch size:** Up to 100 emails per API call (OpenAI supports array input)\n- **Retry logic:** Exponential backoff on 429 rate limit responses\n- **Backfill:** On first deploy, queue all existing emails with `embedding IS NULL`\n- **Frequency:** Process new emails within 60 seconds of insert — near real-time is fine, instant is not required\n\n---\n\n## New API Route\n\n### `GET /api/emails/search?q=your+query&limit=20`\n\n**Flow:**\n\n1. Receive query string from user\n2. Call OpenAI to embed the query (same model, same dimensions)\n3. Run cosine similarity search against `emails` table scoped to `tenant_id`\n4. Return ranked results\n\n**Query:**\n\n```sql\nSELECT\n  id, sender, subject, received_at, recipients,\n  attachments_metadata,\n  LEFT(body_plain_text, 200) AS preview,\n  1 - (embedding <=> $2) AS similarity\nFROM emails\nWHERE\n  tenant_id = $1\n  AND embedding IS NOT NULL\nORDER BY embedding <=> $2\nLIMIT $3;\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"query\": \"invoice payment overdue\",\n  \"data\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": 88,\n      \"sender\": \"billing@vendor.com\",\n      \"subject\": \"Outstanding Balance Reminder\",\n      \"received_at\": \"2026-02-14T09:00:00Z\",\n      \"similarity\": 0.91,\n      \"preview\": \"This is a reminder that your account has an unpaid...\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Hybrid Search (Recommended)\n\nPure vector search occasionally misses obvious keyword matches. Run both in parallel and merge:\n\n```typescript\nasync function hybridSearch(tenantId: string, query: string, limit: number) {\n  const [vectorResults, keywordResults] = await Promise.all([\n    vectorSearch(tenantId, query, limit),\n    keywordSearch(tenantId, query, limit),   // existing ILIKE query\n  ]);\n\n  // Merge by id, boost items that appear in both result sets\n  return mergeAndRank(vectorResults, keywordResults, limit);\n}\n```\n\nSimple merge strategy: deduplicate by `id`, assign a combined score where appearing in both lists gets a 1.2x boost. No ML required.\n\n---\n\n## UI Changes\n\n### Search bar behavior\n\n- Single search input replaces the existing `q` param search\n- On submit, call `/api/emails/search` instead of the list endpoint\n- Show a \"Searching…\" skeleton while the OpenAI embedding call resolves (typically 200–400 ms)\n\n### Results display\n\n- Same `MessageRow` component — no new UI needed\n- Optional: show a subtle similarity confidence indicator (e.g. a muted percentage badge) — omit if it confuses non-technical users\n- Show \"Semantic search powered by OpenAI\" attribution in the footer of results\n\n### Fallback state\n\nIf `embedding IS NULL` for a large portion of the tenant's emails (e.g. backfill still running), show a banner:\n\n> \"Search index is still building — results may be incomplete.\"\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n```bash\nOPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...\nOPENAI_EMBEDDING_MODEL=text-embedding-3-small   # 1536 dims, $0.02/1M tokens\nEMBEDDING_BATCH_SIZE=100\n```\n\n---\n\n## Cost Estimate\n\n| Scenario | Emails | Avg tokens/email | Total tokens | Cost |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Initial backfill | 50,000 | 400 | 20M | ~$0.40 |\n| Initial backfill | 500,000 | 400 | 200M | ~$4.00 |\n| Ongoing (per email) | 1 | 400 | 400 | ~$0.000008 |\n| Per search query | 1 | ~20 | 20 | ~$0.0000004 |\n\nCost is not a meaningful concern at any reasonable scale.\n\n---\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Storing embeddings in a separate vector database (Pinecone, Weaviate) — pgvector is sufficient here\n- Re-embedding when email content is updated (emails are immutable once received)\n- Embedding attachments content (would require OCR / file parsing pipeline)\n- Fine-tuning or custom embedding models",
